Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveThe annual CAF awards held in Rabat, Morocco on Thursday night and the winners have been announced.
Below are the big winners from the continental football award.
Sadio Mane: Senegalese player and new Bayern signee won the African Player of the Year (Men) award for the second consecutive year.
Asisat Oshoala: Nigeriaâ€™s Super Falcons player made history when she won the award on Thursday. She is the only African to have won the Best Player award for five times. A queen in her own rights.
Full list of winners:
Player of the Year (Men): Sadio Mane (Senegal and Bayern Munich)
Player of the Year (Women): Asisat Oshoala (Nigeria and FC Barcelona)
Interclub Player of the Year (Women): Evelyn Badu (Ghana & Sekondi Hasaacas Ladies/Alvaldsnes)
Interclub Player of the Year (Men): Mohamed El Shenawy (Egypt & Al Ahly)
Young Player of the Year (Women): Evelyn Badu (Ghana & Sekondi Hasaacas Ladies/Alvaldsnes)
Young Player of the Year (Men): Pape Matar Sarr (Senegal and Tottenham Hotspur)
Coach of the Year (Women): Desiree Ellis (South Africa)
Coach of the Year (Men): Aliou Cisse (Senegal)
Club of the Year (Women): Mamelodi Sundowns (South Africa)
Club of the Year (Men): Wydad Athletic Club (Morocco)
National Team of the Year (Men): Senegal
Goal of the Year: Pape Ousmane Sakho (Senegal & Simba)
